Syria Plans Investment Fund to Stabilize Financial Market

-- B y   L i n a   I b r a h i m
-- 
2011-09-21T10:44:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/syria-plans-investment-fund-to-stabilize-financial-market.html
Syria ’s government approved the
setting-up of a national fund for investment, with an initial
capital of 2 billion pounds ($41 million), the  Syrian Arab News
Agency  said.  The fund, which can be increased later, will help to
stabilize Syria’s financial market and encourage diversification
of investments, the official agency said, citing Mohamad Nidal al-Shaar, the economy and trade minister.  To contact the reporter on this story:
